Built for the TxODDS World Cup Hackathon. It is anchored to TxLINE's de-vigged
consensus line (TxODDS data), spawns binary YES/NO goal-grain micro-markets on
its own Solana binary escrow-cross venue, and verifies immutable bindings on TxODDS
Merkle-anchored receipt accounts. Finality selection and payout are not claimed here.

Clean-room provenance: all pricing math derives from PUBLIC sources only —
standard proportional de-vig; Avellaneda-Stoikov (2008) and
Guéant-Lehalle-Fernández-Tapia (GLFT) market-making. The on-chain venue and the
settlement/dispute layer are CONSUMED as deployed programs; Roar Markets adds the
per-prop market factory and the consumer surface, not a new venue or oracle. An
exact compiled venue binary is included as a deterministic test fixture, as
attributed below. No proprietary third-party code is included.

This distribution includes material from the Apache-2.0-licensed sibling project:

