Specifically, Roar Markets includes the exact compiled former PitchMaker `pitchmaker_book.so`
at `artifacts/fixtures/pitchmaker_book.so`, sourced from
https://github.com/kamenev72/pitchmaker.git commit
ed567ea53e87329819ac8b98fab2ad1ee3dbb031, repository-relative source path
`artifacts/fixtures/pitchmaker_book.so`. It also includes the Apache-2.0 sibling-derived venue
client, Borsh, discriminator, and transport seam under `packages/core/src/venue/` and `packages/core/src/loop/`,
adapted where needed for Roar Markets' current ABI and in-memory factory integration.

The kickoff-oracle account layouts this repository reads — including the
OuBoundReceipt PDA scheme (["ou_bound", market_id]) — are hand-rolled from public
on-chain formats in `packages/core/src/onchain/`, not copied from a closed source. Solana web3.js,
the Solana client libraries, and Vitest are used under their respective open-source
licenses (see package.json). No code, keys, or data from any closed source are vendored.
